Claims What is claimed is: 1. An integrated circuit comprising: a top; a bottom; four edges including distinct first, second, third, and fourth edges, wherein the second edge is opposite the first edge; a set of digital circuitry pads on the first edge; a set of common RF pads on the second edge opposite the first edge; and at least one set of RF pads on each of the third and fourth edges, each set of RF pads associated with a distinct RF channel. 2. An integrated circuit according to claim 1, wherein the at least one set of RF pads on each of the third and fourth edges comprises at least two sets of RF pads on each of the third and fourth edges. 3. An integrated circuit according to claim 1, wherein the set of common RF pads and each set of RF pads comprises: a central RF pad; and a pair of ground pads positioned on opposing sides of the central RF pad. 4. An integrated circuit according to claim 2, further comprising: at least one ground pad between two sets of RF pads on each of the third and fourth edges. 5. An integrated circuit according to claim 3, further comprising: a ground connection providing an electrical connection from the wide ground plane to at least one ground pad of an RF group. 6. An integrated circuit according to claim 1, wherein the integrated circuit comprises SiGe BiCMOS components. 7. An integrated circuit according to claim 1, wherein each RF channel is configured with both transmit and receive circuitry. 8. An integrated circuit according to claim 1, wherein the integrated circuit is a flip- chip integrated circuit. 9. An integrated circuit according to claim 8, packaged in a wafer level chip scale package (WLCSP). 10. An integrated circuit according to claim 8, packaged in an extended wafer level ball-grid-array (eWLB). 11. A packaged integrated circuit comprising: an integrated circuit including a top; a bottom; four edges including distinct first, second, third, and fourth edges, wherein the second edge is opposite the first edge; a set of digital circuitry pads on the first edge; a set of common RF pads on the second edge opposite the first edge; and at least one set of RF pads on each of the third and fourth edges, each set of RF pads associated with a distinct RF channel; and a leadframe including a set of digital circuitry leads corresponding to the set of digital circuitry pads, a set of common RF leads corresponding to the set of common RF pads, a set of RF leads corresponding to each set of RF pads, and electrical conductors connecting each of said pads of the integrated circuit with a corresponding lead of the leadframe. 12. A packaged integrated circuit according to claim 1 1, wherein the at least one set of RF pads on each of the third and fourth edges comprises at least two sets of RF pads on each of the third and fourth edges. 13. A packaged integrated circuit according to claim 1 1, wherein the set of common RF pads and each set of RF pads comprises: a central RF pad; and a pair of ground pads positioned on opposing sides of the central RF pad. 14. A packaged integrated circuit according to claim 12, further comprising: at least one ground pad between two sets of RF pads on each of the third and fourth edges. 15. A packaged integrated circuit according to claim 13, wherein the leadframe includes a die paddle representing a ground plane, and wherein the integrated circuit includes a ground via providing an electrical connection from the bottom of the integrated circuit between at least one ground pad of an RF group and the die paddle. 16. A packaged integrated circuit according to claim 1 1, wherein at least one pad of the integrated circuit is connected to a corresponding lead of the leadframe using two or more electrical conductors. 17. A packaged integrated circuit according to claim 1 1, wherein the leadframe is between about 5mm to 7mm square. 18. A packaged integrated circuit according to claim 1 1, wherein each RF channel is configured with both transmit and receive circuitry. 